radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; 7 x 9 x 5 cm phlegmon in the right upper quadrant involving the cecum and distal ileum; extensive mesenteric fat stranding; fluid tracking down the right paracolic gutter and collecting within the pelvis; no acute fracture or destructive lesion identified; a single right-sided prominent osteophyte at L1-L2.
